callback_file_request_chunk -> callback_file_chunk_request A couple of minor reasons, combined warrant a PR imo: a) fileChunkRequested is a better signal name than fileRequestChunkReceived, and I don't want to break consistency by reordering words for just this signal b) "request chunk" is parsed by English speakers as a verb-object combination,    implying sending the request, not receiving, whereas "chunk requested" is    parsed (more correctly) as an adjective-noun combo (in particular, request is    a noun not a verb), and thus reads far more like "hey heads up we just got a request"
